power citizens, and in what ways can they be used by governments to control participation? What lessons can be learned from these experiments? Given the growing dissatisfaction with existing democratic systems across the world, this book will be of interest to people seeking innovative ways of deepening democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCitizens' advisory committeeszChile. 0aCitizens' advisory committeeszEcuador. 0aCitizens' advisory committeeszLatin America. 0aCitizens' advisory committeeszVenezuela. 0aPolitical participationzChile. 0aPolitical participationzEcuador. 0aPolitical participationzLatin America. 0aPolitical participationzVenezuela. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Democracy. 4aPolitics and Law : Electoral Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2018z978311149142440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438469195423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438469195/original  a978-3-11-149142-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles